A leading data mining firm claims that between 20 and 50 social media accounts active in Baltimore on Monday were used 825 miles away in Ferguson .
The firm said the link suggests the presence of 'professional protesters' or anarchists who are looking to incite more violence .
Not all the accounts called for outright violence, but at least the tweets were menacing and ominous .
Baltimore's mayor announced a 10 p.m.-5 a.m. curfew would be imposed starting on Tuesday .
Police said on Tuesday that 202 people were arrested, 15 buildings set on fire along with 115 vehicles .